# Content & Lessons Guide

> This guide applies to **every CEFR level** (A1, A2, B1, B2). The same
> templates, types, exercise components, i18n, TTS pipeline and quality
> checklist are shared across all levels. Each level has its own content
> folder; the rest of the platform is level-agnostic.

## Folder Layout (Multi-Level)

```
src/content/
├── shared/                ← types, EXERCISE_TEMPLATES, TEST_TEMPLATES (USED BY ALL LEVELS)
├── a1/
│   ├── lessons/lesson-XX/ ← A1 lesson folders (folder name == lesson id)
│   ├── tests/test-…/
│   └── index.ts           ← A1 registry: loaders, navItems, metadata
├── a2/                    ← same shape
├── b1/, b2/               ← same shape (skeletons)
├── registry.ts            ← global cross-level registry (loaders, lookups)
└── index.ts               ← public barrel: types + helpers + registry
```

When adding a new exercise type, template, or rule, put it in `shared/` so it
is available for every level — never duplicate per level.

## Lesson Folder Structure

Each lesson lives in `src/content/<level>/lessons/<lesson-id>/` with 5 files:

- `metadata.ts` — id, number, title, description, grammarTopics[], vocabulary[]
- `content.ts` — introduction text, dialogues, sections
- `exercises.ts` — ALL lesson elements in PDF order (exercises + НОВИ ДУМИ + ГРАМАТИКА + ДИАЛОЗИ)
- `workbook.ts` — workbook-only exercises
- `index.ts` — re-exports everything as `lessonData`

After creating the files, register the lesson **in the level's index file**
(e.g. `src/content/a2/index.ts`) by adding entries to:

- `<LEVEL>_LESSON_LOADERS` — `'a2-lesson-01': () => import('./lessons/a2-lesson-01')`
- `<LEVEL>_LESSONS_METADATA` — id, number, title, hasTest, testId
- `<LEVEL>_NAV_ITEMS` — sidebar entry
- `<LEVEL>_LESSON_EXERCISE_COUNTS` — total interactive exercises (for sidebar %)

The cross-level `src/content/registry.ts` automatically picks the new entries
up; routes (`/lessons/[lessonId]`, `/tests/[testId]`) work without changes.

## ID Naming Conventions

A1 lesson IDs are kept un-prefixed (`lesson-XX`) for backward compatibility
with existing user progress in the database. **A2 / B1 / B2 lesson IDs are
level-prefixed** (`a2-lesson-XX`, `b1-lesson-XX`, …) so they never collide
with A1.

| Element | A1 format | A2+ format |
|---|---|---|
| Lesson | `lesson-XX` (e.g. `lesson-02`) | `a2-lesson-XX`, `b1-lesson-XX`, … |
| Exercise | `lXX-ex-NN` (e.g. `l02-ex-01`) | `a2-lXX-ex-NN`, `b1-lXX-ex-NN`, … |
| Workbook | `lXX-wb-NN` | `a2-lXX-wb-NN`, … |
| Нови думи | `lXX-novi-dumi-NN` | `a2-lXX-novi-dumi-NN`, … |
| Граматика | `lXX-gramatika-NN` | `a2-lXX-gramatika-NN`, … |
| Диалози | `lXX-dialozi-NN` | `a2-lXX-dialozi-NN`, … |
| Test | `test-a1-N` (e.g. `test-a1-3`) | `test-a2-N`, `test-b1-N`, … |

## Asset Paths

Assets go in `/public/assets/<lesson-id>/` with descriptive subfolders. The
folder name **matches the lesson ID** (so A1 uses `/public/assets/lesson-02/`
and A2 uses `/public/assets/a2-lesson-01/`):

- `audio/tts/` — generated TTS MP3 files (see `tts-audio` rule)
- `audio/` — other audio files
- `exercise-NN-name/` — images for a specific exercise
- `novi-dumi-N-name/` — vocabulary card images
- `gramatika-N/` — grammar section images

Source files (PDFs, audio, images) are on the developer's machine at:
`C:\Users\Work Account\Desktop\CURSOR\GITHUB A1\a1-files\lessons\lesson-X\` (A1)
or the equivalent A2/B1/B2 source folders.

## exercises.ts — Key Rules

- ALL lesson elements go here: exercises AND vocabulary sections AND grammar sections AND dialogues
- The `order` field must match the exact sequence in the PDF
- Informational sections (НОВИ ДУМИ, ГРАМАТИКА, ДИАЛОЗИ) have no `points` field
- Actual exercises have a `points` field
- **`points` = number of blanks/questions, NOT number of sentences.** For `table_fill`, points = number of rows.
- **Do NOT duplicate examples as interactive items.** If `isExample: true`, it must not count toward points.
- Instructions must match the **digital-format standards** — see `content-quality-checklist.mdc` §A3 for the standardized instruction table per exercise type. Do NOT copy verbatim from the textbook; do NOT improvise new instructions for standard exercise types.
- When a lesson has **multiple sections of the same type**, always number them: НОВИ ДУМИ 1, НОВИ ДУМИ 2... / ГРАМАТИКА 1, 2... / ДИАЛОЗИ 1, 2...
- All НОВИ ДУМИ sections in **уроци 0–1 and Азбука** must use instruction: `'Натиснете за произношение.'`
- НОВИ ДУМИ sections in **уроци 2+** use **no instruction** (rely on card-level 🔊 icons only).
- Dialogues: verify **every line** is complete and matches the textbook exactly.
- **Currency rule:** лева → евро, стотинки → евроцента. All monetary exercises must use `dropdown` input (not free text).
- Short fill-in-blank exercises (e.g., два/две, какъв/каква) → use `layout: 'two-column'`.
- `content.ts` dialogues **must match** `exercises.ts` dialogues exactly (same lines, same prices, same currency).
- Empty `imageUrl: ''` is safe — components (`IllustratedCards`, `GrammarWithExamples`) skip rendering when empty.
- **`grammar_examples` label field:** Use `label` for visual-only annotations (e.g. `'Какъв — мъжки род'`). Shown as a green badge below the card content. **NOT read by TTS** — keeps audio clean while displaying grammatical info.
- **Content guideline for TTS:** In dialogue lines with numbers/sums, prefer a **period** over a dash (e.g. `'Рестото. Четири евро.'` not `'Рестото — четири евро.'`). The dash confuses TTS pronunciation and pacing.
- **`grammar_table` alignment rule:** `columns.length` MUST equal `cells.length` for every row. The `pronoun` field renders in the first column automatically (with an empty header). Do NOT include the pronoun column label in `columns` — it causes header misalignment.
- **`grammar_table` bolding — choose the right tool:** `boldColumns: [n]` bolds the ENTIRE column (header + cells). Inline `**word**` inside a cell bolds ONLY that word/ending (e.g. „пазар**ът**", „две ябълк**и**"). Use inline `**` when you want to highlight noun endings / articles per word — using `boldColumns` would make the table heavy and unreadable. Markdown is stripped before TTS.
- **Instruction text must match the actual exercise type.** If the exercise uses dropdowns, the instruction should say "Изберете" (Select), not "Напишете" (Write). Match the verb to the interaction: Select → dropdown, Write → text input, Arrange → drag-and-drop.

## Grammar Reference (`grammarReference` on `LessonContent`)

Each lesson can have a structured grammar reference attached to its `content.ts`:

```ts
// src/content/<level>/lessons/<lesson-id>/content.ts
export const content: LessonContent = {
  // ...
  grammarReference: [
    {
      id: 'l07-gr-redni-chislitelni',
      title: { bg: '...', en: '...', fr: '...', ar: '...', fa: '...', ru: '...', uk: '...' },
      content: { bg: '...', en: '...', fr: '...', ar: '...', fa: '...', ru: '...', uk: '...' },
    },
    // ...more grammar topics for THIS lesson only
  ],
};
```

**Where it appears (automatic — no UI work needed):**
The `<GrammarReferenceSection>` component is rendered TWICE on every lesson page — once at the **TOP** (right after the cultural notes, before the exercises) and once at the **BOTTOM** (right after the exercises, before the workbook „Преговор"). Both render identically. See `platform-ui` rule → "Grammar Reference Placement" for the implementation.

**Authoring rules:**
- Title MUST be filled on **all 7 languages** (`bg`, `en`, `fr`, `ar`, `fa`, `ru`, `uk`).
- Content MUST be filled on **all 7 languages** — written manually with high quality. **Do NOT rely on web/auto translation** for grammar — linguistic terminology gets mangled.
- Use prose style (not Markdown tables) — paragraphs with inline examples in Bulgarian + native-language explanations in parentheses.
- Bulgarian examples in the body **stay in Bulgarian** even in the other-language versions — the learner needs to see the original form.
- Cover only the grammar that is **introduced in THIS lesson** — not foundational grammar from earlier lessons.
- Use `id` format: `l<NN>-gr-<topic-slug>` (e.g. `l07-gr-redni-chislitelni`). For A2+: `a2-l<NN>-gr-...`.
- Reference lesson 6's `grammarReference` as the canonical pedagogical template (4 grammar sections, prose style, examples in Bulgarian with translations in parentheses).

## Grammar Info Box (`grammar_highlight`)

For visually prominent grammar notes that need to stand out from the exercise body (e.g. the с/със rule in l2 ex 12, or the million/milliard rule in l5 ex 31), add a `grammarHighlight` object to the exercise:

```ts
grammarHighlight: {
  textKey: 'exercise.sSusWith',  // key in ui.ts (pre-translated on 7 languages)
  // OR inline text if translation will be auto:
  // text: 'Когато дума след „с" ...',
}
```

The component renders it as a green info box with an „ℹ" icon above the exercise body. Add the translation key to `src/i18n/ui.ts` on all 7 languages.

## Exercise Types — 5 Categories

**НОВИ ДУМИ (FREQUENT):** `illustrated_cards`

**ГРАМАТИКА (FREQUENT):** `grammar_visual`, `grammar_examples`, `grammar_table`

**ДИАЛОЗИ И ТЕКСТОВЕ (FREQUENT):** `dialogues`, `reading_text`

**УПРАЖНЕНИЯ — Чести (FREQUENT):** `fill_in_blank`, `workbook_fill_blank`, `multiple_choice`, `dropdown_match`, `word_order`, `table_fill`, `personal_choice`

**УПРАЖНЕНИЯ — Редки (RARE):** `match_pairs`, `letter_choice`, `image_labeling`, `syllable_blocks`, `word_search`, `true_false`, `dialogue_builder`, `fill_with_images`

**ИНТЕРАКТИВНИ / АЗБУКА:** `connect_dots` (змия — проследи буквите по ред), `alphabet_maze` (лабиринт — намери пътя по азбучен ред)

**Not yet implemented (show placeholder):** `verb_conjugation`, `number_writing`, `dialogue_reading`, `text_comprehension`, `listening`

## Textbook → Exercise Type Mappings

Use these mappings when digitalizing textbook exercises:

| Textbook pattern | Exercise type |
|---|---|
| "Подредете буквите" | `syllable_blocks` |
| "Открийте скритите думи" | `word_search` |
| "Подредете фразите" | `dialogue_builder` |
| "Вярно или грешно" | `true_false` |
| "Отговорете на въпросите" | `dropdown_match` |
| "Напишете в правилната форма" | `workbook_fill_blank` |
| Граматична таблица | `grammar_table` |
| Нови думи с картинки | `illustrated_cards` |
| Диалози | `dialogues` |
| "Прочетете текста" | `reading_text` |
| "Попълнете таблицата" (род/мн.ч.) | `table_fill` |
| "Какво обичате / Напишете какво обичате" | `personal_choice` (points: 0) |
| Парични упражнения (цени, ресто) | `dropdown_match` (never free text) |
| "Свържете/проследете буквите по ред" | `connect_dots` (змия) |
| "Намерете пътя в лабиринта" | `alphabet_maze` (интерактивна решетка) |
| Нови думи БЕЗ картинки (международни думи и др.) | `illustrated_cards` (imageUrl: '') |

## Content Quality Standards (from feedback on lessons 0–6)

See `content-quality-checklist` rule for the FULL checklist. Key rules to remember here:

- **Instructions adapted for digital:** Do NOT copy textbook instructions verbatim. The textbook is paper — our platform is interactive. Every instruction must describe what the user does IN THE APP (dropdown → „Изберете", drag → „Плъзнете", etc.). Remove paper references: „по двойки", „на хартия", „в тетрадката".
- **No component shuffle:** `word_order.words[]`, `syllable_blocks.syllables[]`, `dialogue_builder.sentences[]` — the component does NOT shuffle. Elements show EXACTLY in array order. Arrange them maximally scrambled when defining the content.
- **Mix true/false:** In `true_false` and checklist exercises, interleave correct and incorrect items (never group all correct first).
- **Numbers as words for TTS:** In `listeningText` and text paragraphs meant for audio, write numbers as words (76 → „седемдесет и шест") so TTS pronounces them correctly.
- **First word capitalized:** Every sentence in options, true_false items, and table cells must start with a capital letter.
- **No definite article with possessives:** „баба" not „бабата" when preceded by a possessive pronoun (моята баба).
- **Review section:** Title is „Преговор", subtitle is „Упражнения за затвърждаване на наученото". Never use „от работната тетрадка".
- **Grammar table subtitle → subtext:** Explanatory text goes as grey subtext under the exercise title, never as a separate boxed block.
- **textTitle for reading_text:** When a text has a title (e.g. „България е хубава страна"), set `textTitle` to show it bold above the paragraphs.
- **showDictionary for reading_text:** Set `showDictionary: true` on reading exercises with real vocabulary (not on test exercises with `noTranslation`).
- **НОВИ ДУМИ before exercises:** Vocabulary sections must come BEFORE exercises that use those words. If a reading text uses new vocabulary, place the text AFTER the НОВИ ДУМИ section.
- **Grammar rule before practice:** If an exercise applies a grammar rule (e.g. articles), the rule must be shown BEFORE the exercise.

### Pre-translation (`instructionKey`) rules

Grammar instructions and complex exercise instructions MUST be pre-translated via `instructionKey` in `ui.ts`. Auto-translation (`useTranslate`) is NOT reliable for:
- Linguistic terminology (род, член, спрежение, множествено число...)
- Instructions describing new interaction patterns (drag, swipe, column sorting...)
- Grammar notes with Bulgarian-specific examples

Simple, repetitive instructions (e.g. „Попълнете празните места.") can use auto-translation.

## Automatic UI Behaviors (no action needed in content files)

The following behaviors are built into the exercise components — content authors don't need to do anything extra:

- **Options are shuffled** — `WorkbookFillBlank` shuffles `options[]` on render so the correct answer isn't always first.
- **Letters are shuffled** — `LetterChoice` shuffles the letter pool on render.
- **Reset button** — ALL interactive exercise components show a "Reset" button. If a component is missing one, it is a bug — report/fix it.
- **TTS** — Components prefer pre-generated MP3 via `getTtsAudioPath()`, with browser `speakBulgarian()` as fallback. See `tts-audio` rule for generation details.

## Alternative Correct Answers

When an exercise has **multiple valid answers** for the same question:

**`dropdown_match`** — use `alternateCorrectAnswers`:
```ts
{ id: 'q2', left: 'Добър', options: [...], correctAnswer: 'ден!', alternateCorrectAnswers: ['вечер!'] }
```

**`dialogue_builder`** — use `alternateOrders` on the section:
```ts
{ id: 'в.', givenFirstLine: '...', sentences: [...], alternateOrders: [[...], [...]] }
```

**`workbook_fill_blank`** — use `acceptableAnswers`:
```ts
{ text: '...', correctAnswers: ['тя е украинка.'], acceptableAnswers: [['тя е украинка', 'тя е украинка.']] }
```

## Creating Exercises — ALWAYS Use Templates

When creating exercises, **always read [src/content/shared/EXERCISE_TEMPLATES.ts](mdc:src/content/shared/EXERCISE_TEMPLATES.ts) first**.
Copy the relevant template and replace only the content — never write exercise structure from scratch.

Reference: [LESSON_STRUCTURE.md](mdc:LESSON_STRUCTURE.md) shows how lesson-01 PDF maps to exercise types and IDs.

## Adding a New Exercise Type — Checklist

New exercise types live in `shared/` so they are immediately available for
every CEFR level.

1. Add interface + type to [src/content/shared/types.ts](mdc:src/content/shared/types.ts)
   (the legacy alias `@/content/types` still works — it re-exports from `shared/`)
2. Create component in `src/components/exercises/`
3. Add `case` in [src/components/exercises/ExerciseRenderer.tsx](mdc:src/components/exercises/ExerciseRenderer.tsx)
4. Add template to [src/content/shared/EXERCISE_TEMPLATES.ts](mdc:src/content/shared/EXERCISE_TEMPLATES.ts)
5. Add type to the category list in this rule
